description:
**Problem**
~16k lines of integration tests in \`beads-rs/tests/integration/\` currently import daemon internals via \`beads_rs::daemon::*\`. After the daemon runtime moves to beads-daemon and beads-rs stops exporting daemon internals, these tests need a new access path. Without an intentional test surface, tests will either break or we'll be forced to make too many daemon internals public.

**Design**
Add a \`test-harness\` feature to beads-daemon that exposes a \`testkit\` module with an explicit allowlist of internal types tests are permitted to use.

\`\`\`rust
// crates/beads-daemon/src/lib.rs
#[cfg(any(test, feature = "test-harness"))]
pub mod testkit;

// crates/beads-daemon/src/testkit/mod.rs
//! Explicit allowlist of daemon internals for integration testing.
//! Adding to this list is a deliberate boundary decision.

pub mod repl {
    pub use crate::runtime::repl::session::{Session, SessionConfig, SessionPhase, ...};
    pub use beads_daemon_core::repl::proto::{ReplEnvelope, ReplMessage, ...};
    pub use beads_daemon_core::repl::frame::{FrameReader, FrameWriter, ...};
}

pub mod wal {
    pub use beads_daemon_core::wal::{SqliteWalIndex, SegmentWriter, ...};
}

pub mod store {
    pub use crate::runtime::store::lock::{StoreLock, StoreLockError, read_lock_meta};
}

pub mod mutation {
    pub use crate::runtime::mutation_engine::{MutationEngine, MutationContext, ...};
}
\`\`\`

Then migrate all test fixtures:
- \`beads_rs::daemon::wal::*\` → \`beads_daemon::testkit::wal::*\` or \`beads_daemon_core::wal::*\`
- \`beads_rs::daemon::repl::*\` → \`beads_daemon::testkit::repl::*\`
- \`beads_rs::daemon::ipc::*\` → \`beads_surface::ipc::*\` (already partially migrated)
- \`beads_rs::daemon::ops::*\` → \`beads_daemon::testkit::ops::*\`
- \`beads_rs::daemon::store_lock::*\` → \`beads_daemon::testkit::store::*\`

Move integration tests that test daemon internals into \`crates/beads-daemon/tests/\`.
Keep e2e/CLI tests in \`crates/beads-rs/tests/\` (they test the binary).

**Acceptance**
- [ ] \`beads-daemon\` has \`test-harness\` feature exposing \`testkit\` module
- [ ] Testkit module has documented, explicit allowlist of re-exported internals
- [ ] Zero \`beads_rs::daemon::*\` imports in any test file
- [ ] Daemon-internal integration tests (WAL, repl, store lock, mutation) moved to \`crates/beads-daemon/tests/\`
- [ ] E2E/CLI tests remain in \`crates/beads-rs/tests/\` using only public APIs
- [ ] \`fixtures/daemon_boundary.rs\` deleted or migrated
- [ ] \`cargo test --workspace\` passes
- [ ] \`cargo test --workspace --features beads-daemon/test-harness\` passes

**Files:** \`crates/beads-daemon/src/testkit/\` (new), \`crates/beads-daemon/tests/\` (new, tests moved from beads-rs), \`crates/beads-rs/tests/integration/\` (shrink), \`crates/beads-rs/tests/integration/fixtures/daemon_boundary.rs\` (delete)
